# Summer Film: Scene-by-Scene Analysis & Improvement Guide

This artifact provides a structured breakdown of the current script, identifying the narrative "hits" and "misses" to help refine the story flow, character arcs, and technical world-building.

## Core Themes & Observations
- **Strengths**: The "acoustic horror/mystery" angle is unique and evocative. The dynamic between Dallas (grief-stricken scientist) and the kids (tech-savvy, curious) works well. The "115.3" through-line with Mr. Mike is a strong mystery hook.
- **Weaknesses**: Script-level inconsistencies (creature escaping/not escaping), clunky dialogue in high-tension moments, and slightly repetitive "hum/vibration" descriptions.

